potential_causes.suggestion_localized: Maintaining hormonal balance through lifestyle and diet.
potential_causes.explanation_localized: At age 50, hormonal fluctuations, especially related to menopause, can influence conditions like endometriosis.

potential_causes.suggestion_localized: Incorporate stress reduction techniques like mindfulness and relaxation exercises.
potential_causes.explanation_localized: Stress can worsen symptoms or influence the perception of pain associated with endometriosis.

potential_causes.suggestion_localized: Follow an anti-inflammatory diet rich in fruits, vegetables, and omega-3 fatty acids.
potential_causes.explanation_localized: Dietary factors can impact inflammation levels, which may affect endometriosis symptoms.

potential_causes.suggestion_localized: Engage in regular, gentle exercise suitable for your condition.
potential_causes.explanation_localized: Regular physical activity can help reduce pain and improve overall well-being.

potential_causes.suggestion_localized: Establish a consistent sleep schedule and relaxing bedtime routine.
potential_causes.explanation_localized: Adequate restorative sleep can influence hormonal health and pain perception.

potential_causes.suggestion_localized: Create a comfortable and calming environment at home and work.
potential_causes.explanation_localized: Environmental stressors like noise and lighting can exacerbate pain and discomfort.

potential_causes.suggestion_localized: Review medications and supplements with a healthcare provider for potential impacts.
potential_causes.explanation_localized: Certain medications or supplements might influence hormonal or inflammatory processes.
